HEADWORD: Nemean
<hw>Ne"me*an</hw> <pr>(n⟦emac⟧"m⟦esl⟧*⟦ait⟧n; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Nemeus</ets>, fr. <ets>Nemea</ets>, Gr.
<grk>Neme`h</grk>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Nemea, in Argolis,
where the ancient Greeks celebrated games, and Hercules killed a
lion.</def>⟦br⟧
